# Cursor Rules — xdc-node-setup

## Project Context

This is the operational toolkit for XDC Network multi-client node infrastructure.
Clients: geth/XDC (go-ethereum fork), Erigon, Nethermind, Reth.
Networks: Mainnet (chain 50), Apothem testnet (chain 51).
Consensus: XDPoS v2 (HotStuff BFT, 108 validators, 900-block epochs).

## Coding Standards

- All scripts: `#!/usr/bin/env bash` + `set -euo pipefail`
- Variables: `readonly UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for constants, allow env override with `${VAR:-default}`
- Functions: `lower_snake_case`, always `local` variables
- Logging: `[$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)] message` format
- Always add `--dry-run` support to scripts that modify state
- Source shared libs: `source "${LIB_DIR}/common.sh"` when available

## Port Reference (Mainnet)

| Client     | RPC  | WS   | P2P   |
|------------|------|------|-------|
| geth       | 8545 | 8549 | 30303 |
| erigon     | 8547 | 8548 | 30305 |
| nethermind | 8548 | 8553 | 30304 |
| reth       | 8588 | —    | 30306 |

## Key Files

- `.agent/CONTEXT.md` — ports, clients, quirks (read first)
- `.agent/CONVENTIONS.md` — full coding standards
- `configs/ports.env` — all port definitions
- `scripts/lib/` — shared bash libraries
- `agents/` — AI agent personas

## Commit Format

`<type>(<scope>): <description>`
Types: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore, ci

## When Writing Scripts

1. Add header block with Usage and Issue link
2. Define config vars at top with env overrides
3. Support `--dry-run` for destructive operations
4. Log to stdout with timestamp prefix
5. Output structured JSON to `data/` subdirectories
6. `chmod +x` all scripts

## Don't Do

- Don't hardcode ports (use variables referencing configs/ports.env values)
- Don't expose RPC to 0.0.0.0 without auth
- Don't commit secrets or API keys
- Don't use `rm -rf` without confirmation
- Don't break `set -euo pipefail` semantics (quote variables, check return codes)
